1
00:00:01,200 --> 00:00:02,300
I'm counting on you.

2
00:00:08,640 --> 00:00:09,870
That's a very natural smile.

3
00:00:10,220 --> 00:00:11,220
What a shame.

4
00:00:12,880 --> 00:00:13,880
Awesome!

5
00:00:15,300 --> 00:00:16,500
(Day 45)

6
00:00:16,540 --> 00:00:17,610
What is this?

7
00:00:18,240 --> 00:00:19,409
If we leave Itsuki-san to his own devices,

8
00:00:19,410 --> 00:00:21,419
he'll just play mobile games all day.

9
00:00:21,420 --> 00:00:22,650
So I decided to take him out.

10
00:00:22,720 --> 00:00:24,160
That's not what I'm talking about...

11
00:00:24,240 --> 00:00:25,969
So Hasegawa-san is
living at your place now?

12
00:00:25,970 --> 00:00:26,970
Oh, no, that's not it...

13
00:00:27,060 --> 00:00:28,260
But don't worry about it.

14
00:00:28,460 --> 00:00:29,809
He cooks delicious meals,

15
00:00:29,810 --> 00:00:31,770
so it's actually a win-win for me.

16
00:00:31,990 --> 00:00:34,640
How could you make
that decision on your own?

17
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:37,570
- What's going on?
- Honestly...

18
00:00:38,140 --> 00:00:41,600
Yamada let Hasegawa-san
move in without asking.

19
00:00:44,680 --> 00:00:45,940
Did Yamada take this?

20
00:00:47,840 --> 00:00:48,840
It's on sale!

21
00:00:49,880 --> 00:00:51,240
Meat! Let's have a barbecue! Meat!

22
00:00:51,550 --> 00:00:52,480
Isn't that a bit too fast?

23
00:00:52,480 --> 00:00:53,140
Huh?

24
00:00:53,141 --> 00:00:54,661
We haven't even done the vegetables...

25
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:56,280
It's fine, it's fine.

26
00:00:57,240 --> 00:00:58,880
Didn't you get some really natural shots?

27
00:00:59,220 --> 00:01:00,550
It's a huge success.

28
00:01:00,590 --> 00:01:01,590
Wait, what?

29
00:01:02,060 --> 00:01:03,060
No, listen.

30
00:01:03,160 --> 00:01:04,629
Shiho, weren't you sighing about

31
00:01:04,630 --> 00:01:08,630
not being able to capture
Hasegawa's natural side?

32
00:01:09,040 --> 00:01:10,099
That's why

33
00:01:10,100 --> 00:01:13,380
I asked Yamada to take him out for drinks.

34
00:01:14,140 --> 00:01:15,720
Looks like my plan worked perfectly.

35
00:01:16,860 --> 00:01:19,460
I'd appreciate it if you didn't
take matters into your own hands.

36
00:01:20,280 --> 00:01:21,419
Getting too close to the subject

37
00:01:21,420 --> 00:01:23,139
isn't good for a documentary.

38
00:01:23,140 --> 00:01:25,560
And this is far from being natural.

39
00:01:26,340 --> 00:01:29,460
You should trust Yamada a bit more.

40
00:01:30,380 --> 00:01:31,709
If you do,

41
00:01:31,710 --> 00:01:34,920
it'll make things easier
for you too, Shiho.

42
00:01:36,690 --> 00:01:37,330
Right.

43
00:01:37,330 --> 00:01:38,330
Is that so bad?

44
00:01:39,140 --> 00:01:39,830
You have a point.

45
00:01:39,830 --> 00:01:40,760
Exactly.

46
00:01:40,761 --> 00:01:42,641
You're not smiling but
actually angry, are you?

47
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:44,860
- I'm sorry.
- Good.

48
00:02:21,100 --> 00:02:28,100
"The Boy and I Who Will Break Up in 100 Days"
(Episode 4)

49
00:02:31,040 --> 00:02:32,810
You're already at level 80?

50
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:35,220
How many hours a day do you play?

51
00:02:35,880 --> 00:02:39,119
Probably about 36 hours.

52
00:02:39,120 --> 00:02:40,500
Unemployed people are terrifying.

53
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:42,200
So scary.

54
00:02:43,330 --> 00:02:44,080
Um...

55
00:02:44,081 --> 00:02:47,200
I heard he's been staying
at Yamada's place for a week now.

56
00:02:47,330 --> 00:02:49,200
- I'm so sorry.
- Oh, no, don't worry about it.

57
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:50,740
(Day 49)
Please don't apologize.

58
00:02:51,140 --> 00:02:53,140
Itsuki is the one who's
overstaying his welcome.

59
00:02:57,860 --> 00:02:58,860
Um...

60
00:03:01,100 --> 00:03:03,110
Has Yamada-san mentioned anything to you?

61
00:03:03,150 --> 00:03:04,010
Huh?

62
00:03:04,110 --> 00:03:05,110
Like, you know...

63
00:03:05,360 --> 00:03:07,959
Has he said anything
about living with Itsuki?

64
00:03:07,960 --> 00:03:09,280
Like how they're getting along...

65
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:11,200
Oh, sorry.

66
00:03:11,240 --> 00:03:12,440
- Forget I asked.
- No...

67
00:03:14,060 --> 00:03:15,060
I suppose...

68
00:03:15,920 --> 00:03:17,040
I guess that's how it is.

69
00:03:17,060 --> 00:03:18,329
I'm really sorry.

70
00:03:18,330 --> 00:03:19,890
- I'm so sorry.
- No, really, it's fine.

71
00:03:20,460 --> 00:03:23,130
We're about halfway through filming, right?

72
00:03:23,520 --> 00:03:24,600
How is it going?

73
00:03:25,080 --> 00:03:26,269
You call it "footage," right?

74
00:03:26,270 --> 00:03:28,800
Oh, that's all thanks to you two.

75
00:03:31,620 --> 00:03:32,620
As for me...

76
00:03:33,620 --> 00:03:39,450
I actually hoped your project would fail.

77
00:03:42,380 --> 00:03:45,390
But I think this is going to
be an amazing documentary.

78
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:48,800
Oh I don't think so.

79
00:03:48,900 --> 00:03:52,160
- That's impossible.
- Hey, over here!

80
00:03:53,700 --> 00:03:55,000
Whoa!

81
00:03:55,920 --> 00:03:57,440
What a huge house!

82
00:03:58,580 --> 00:04:00,879
It feels a hundred times
bigger than Yama-chan's place.

83
00:04:00,880 --> 00:04:03,259
Hey! You're the one
sleeping there right now.

84
00:04:03,260 --> 00:04:05,980
I can't believe the two of us
managed to sleep in such a tiny space.

85
00:04:14,780 --> 00:04:15,580
- Okay, thank you.
- Sure.

86
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:17,000
Thank you all for your cooperation.

87
00:04:17,180 --> 00:04:19,029
Kayano-san brought some treats.

88
00:04:19,030 --> 00:04:20,139
Let's all share them.

89
00:04:20,140 --> 00:04:21,140
Oh, thank you.

90
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:22,160
Should we film this?

91
00:04:22,340 --> 00:04:23,809
No, it's fine. Sorry, but could
you come with me for a second?

92
00:04:23,810 --> 00:04:24,810
Here, help yourself.

93
00:04:32,060 --> 00:04:33,980
I'm moving back to your
place starting tomorrow.

94
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:36,940
Huh? That's so sudden.

95
00:04:38,200 --> 00:04:39,940
Yama-chan told me to go back.

96
00:04:40,340 --> 00:04:42,340
Oh, I see.

97
00:04:44,010 --> 00:04:45,710
Did you say something to Kayano-san?

98
00:04:45,950 --> 00:04:46,780
Hmm?

99
00:04:46,880 --> 00:04:49,950
Yama-chan just got chewed out over there.

100
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:51,800
Poor guy.

101
00:04:56,060 --> 00:04:57,060
Ah.

102
00:04:59,420 --> 00:05:00,640
I won.

103
00:05:03,080 --> 00:05:04,080
Hey.

104
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:07,400
Should we show this to your grandparents?

105
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:09,000
Huh?

106
00:05:09,120 --> 00:05:10,740
Show them what?

107
00:05:12,400 --> 00:05:16,080
Like this, to show them you're dating.

108
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:22,000
What should we do?

109
00:05:24,640 --> 00:05:26,120
There's no way we can say no to this.

110
00:05:27,820 --> 00:05:28,920
I guess so...

111
00:05:50,400 --> 00:05:51,739
Is not wearing it even an option?

112
00:05:51,740 --> 00:05:53,420
- No.
- I figured.

113
00:06:01,020 --> 00:06:04,190
Your parents are really wonderful people.

114
00:06:06,100 --> 00:06:07,100
Yeah.

115
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:13,870
Your grandparents must've be wonderful too.

116
00:06:24,590 --> 00:06:25,590
That's why

117
00:06:28,030 --> 00:06:29,850
I really don't want to lie to them.

118
00:06:39,790 --> 00:06:42,190
How long do you plan to keep this up?

119
00:06:44,670 --> 00:06:48,400
Once filming ends,
are you just going to say, "Okay, goodbye"?

120
00:06:49,890 --> 00:06:53,010
Or will we wait until it airs?

121
00:06:54,550 --> 00:06:56,650
And what happens after it airs?

122
00:06:57,810 --> 00:07:02,720
To the people who watch this documentary
about this "wonderful couple,"

123
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:06,420
can you really tell them,
"Actually, we broke up a long time ago"?

124
00:07:09,170 --> 00:07:12,260
In that case... why don't
we just stay together?

125
00:07:24,010 --> 00:07:27,810
If we don't break up,
there won't be any problem.

126
00:07:34,230 --> 00:07:35,230
I think

127
00:07:36,430 --> 00:07:38,350
the dead can't be brought back to life.

128
00:07:46,610 --> 00:07:49,500
(Day 62) Now, if I may,
I'd like to propose a toast.

129
00:07:49,930 --> 00:07:51,269
Kasuga-san, Kubota-san,

130
00:07:51,270 --> 00:07:53,540
congratulations on your
proposal being selected!

131
00:07:53,650 --> 00:07:55,369
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

132
00:07:55,370 --> 00:07:57,269
- Yes! We did it!
- You're too loud.

133
00:07:57,270 --> 00:07:58,459
Sorry, sorry.

134
00:07:58,460 --> 00:07:59,916
- Congratulations, you two.
- Thank you.

135
00:07:59,940 --> 00:08:00,710
Great job.

136
00:08:00,710 --> 00:08:01,710
Thank you.

137
00:08:04,050 --> 00:08:06,349
Once I learned the project leader was gay,

138
00:08:06,350 --> 00:08:07,720
it all made sense.

139
00:08:08,550 --> 00:08:11,590
No wonder the female characters
have such strong agency.

140
00:08:12,090 --> 00:08:14,159
Walking a path different from others

141
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:15,510
must have been very difficult.

142
00:08:16,370 --> 00:08:18,659
But in this visual design,

143
00:08:18,660 --> 00:08:21,950
his unique sensibility as a sexual
minority really shines through.

144
00:08:22,890 --> 00:08:25,130
Conveying diversity through this ad...

145
00:08:26,330 --> 00:08:27,770
What was that all about?

146
00:08:29,170 --> 00:08:31,730
That was a textbook microaggression.

147
00:08:32,270 --> 00:08:33,409
Saying that because you're gay,

148
00:08:33,410 --> 00:08:35,410
you can depict women with such agency.

149
00:08:37,150 --> 00:08:37,950
Exactly.

150
00:08:37,980 --> 00:08:43,220
And almost all the parts they praised
were actually Kubota-san's ideas.

151
00:08:44,850 --> 00:08:47,889
Yet they attribute it to some
"sexual minority sensibility."

152
00:08:47,890 --> 00:08:50,230
What a load of nonsense, right?

153
00:08:52,030 --> 00:08:54,730
But you're the one who
brought it all together.

154
00:08:55,130 --> 00:08:57,330
That doesn't mean your
sensibility didn't play a part.

155
00:09:00,210 --> 00:09:04,040
Maybe some people did judge
you based on your identity this time,

156
00:09:04,310 --> 00:09:06,780
but that's still a part
of who you are, isn't it?

157
00:09:08,030 --> 00:09:11,410
You won this pitch on your own merit.

158
00:09:13,490 --> 00:09:14,950
Is there a problem with that?

159
00:09:21,150 --> 00:09:22,349
Excuse me.

160
00:09:22,350 --> 00:09:25,750
I'm going to the restroom to
splash some water on my face.

161
00:09:26,090 --> 00:09:27,469
- Up we go.
- Are you okay?

162
00:09:27,470 --> 00:09:28,529
Are you alright?

163
00:09:28,530 --> 00:09:29,950
Excuse me...

164
00:09:45,950 --> 00:09:47,920
Winning a pitch because you're gay...

165
00:09:47,950 --> 00:09:50,020
is that really so hard to accept?

166
00:09:53,070 --> 00:09:55,670
Don't they have affirmative
action systems abroad?

167
00:09:55,730 --> 00:09:58,330
Giving more opportunities
based on being a sexual minority

168
00:09:58,360 --> 00:10:00,326
can actually be seen as a good
thing from a certain perspective.

169
00:10:00,350 --> 00:10:02,170
Can't we look at it that way?

170
00:10:02,750 --> 00:10:03,979
On one hand, you want
to be treated as special,

171
00:10:03,980 --> 00:10:05,669
but on the other hand, you
don't want to be treated differently.

172
00:10:05,670 --> 00:10:08,470
I feel like those two demands are
getting mixed up. Isn't that a bit...

173
00:10:12,030 --> 00:10:13,150
confusing for everyone else?

174
00:10:18,950 --> 00:10:21,920
Please make sure to include
this interview in the documentary.

175
00:10:23,210 --> 00:10:25,430
I can't promise you that.

176
00:10:26,020 --> 00:10:27,719
The existence of this documentary

177
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:30,560
was ultimately the deciding
factor in winning this pitch.

178
00:10:30,590 --> 00:10:35,330
Just like vegetables labeled
with the grower's face on them,

179
00:10:35,860 --> 00:10:40,200
the client seems to want to market
Kasuga-san and the documentary as a package.

180
00:10:45,810 --> 00:10:47,250
I'll definitely consider it...

181
00:10:54,470 --> 00:10:55,720
As for me...

182
00:10:59,730 --> 00:11:02,089
I just want to be treated as a human being.

183
00:11:02,090 --> 00:11:02,710
Yes.

184
00:11:02,760 --> 00:11:05,829
I want them to treat Kasuga Yuma

185
00:11:05,830 --> 00:11:10,500
simply as Kasuga Yuma.

186
00:11:10,800 --> 00:11:13,500
Really, that's all.

187
00:11:13,870 --> 00:11:15,540
- Do you understand?
- I do.

188
00:11:16,370 --> 00:11:17,910
- I get it.
- Oh?

189
00:11:18,670 --> 00:11:20,869
Like being asked to "give
a woman's perspective,"

190
00:11:20,870 --> 00:11:23,650
or hearing "it's so
lively with a girl around."

191
00:11:23,810 --> 00:11:25,049
You think you're talking about work,

192
00:11:25,050 --> 00:11:26,450
but then they start hitting on you.

193
00:11:26,850 --> 00:11:27,660
I often feel that way too.

194
00:11:27,660 --> 00:11:31,490
I don't want to be treated as a woman, I
just want to be treated as a human being.

195
00:11:31,520 --> 00:11:32,920
Exactly! Right?

196
00:11:33,090 --> 00:11:34,320
- Yes.
- See?

197
00:11:34,930 --> 00:11:38,960
Wow, Kayano-san, you understand
me way better than Itsuki does.

198
00:11:40,500 --> 00:11:42,390
- Right?
- Yes, yes, yes.

199
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:48,709
I'm going to make a documentary
that treats Kasuga-san as a human being.

200
00:11:48,710 --> 00:11:49,710
Yeah.

201
00:11:49,770 --> 00:11:54,010
And I'll use this film to change this society
that refuses to treat Kasuga-san as a human being.

202
00:11:54,490 --> 00:11:55,556
That's the only thing I want to do.

203
00:11:55,580 --> 00:11:57,410
Alright! That's great!

204
00:11:57,930 --> 00:11:58,970
I'm counting on you, then.

205
00:11:59,070 --> 00:12:00,289
- Please, I'm counting on you.
- Leave it to me.

206
00:12:00,290 --> 00:12:01,909
- Let's make it together.
- I will make it happen.

207
00:12:01,910 --> 00:12:02,910
Whoa!

208
00:12:03,830 --> 00:12:05,430
If you're going to throw up, do it here!

209
00:12:12,830 --> 00:12:14,399
Could I get a glass of water?

210
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:15,529
Wait... Hold on.

211
00:12:15,530 --> 00:12:17,230
Just hang in there a little longer.

212
00:12:25,010 --> 00:12:25,570
Ah...

213
00:12:25,571 --> 00:12:27,709
Yamada! Yamada! Yamada!

214
00:12:27,710 --> 00:12:28,710
Whoa!

215
00:12:30,180 --> 00:12:31,180
Huh?

216
00:12:31,590 --> 00:12:32,850
You're back pretty early.

217
00:12:38,270 --> 00:12:40,690
I really respect you guys.

218
00:12:46,800 --> 00:12:48,700
Wait... Hold on.

219
00:12:59,240 --> 00:13:00,330
Did he throw up?

220
00:13:00,610 --> 00:13:01,810
Poor thing.

221
00:13:04,850 --> 00:13:06,110
Um... Well...

222
00:13:09,870 --> 00:13:11,190
I'm so sorry.

223
00:13:15,510 --> 00:13:16,510
Hey, you.

224
00:13:17,210 --> 00:13:18,290
You can go home now.

225
00:13:19,830 --> 00:13:20,970
Huh? But...

226
00:13:22,310 --> 00:13:23,969
What a pain. Just go home.

227
00:13:23,970 --> 00:13:25,050
Take your clothes with you.

228
00:13:37,690 --> 00:13:39,010
What on earth is going on?

229
00:13:39,990 --> 00:13:41,220
What does it matter?

230
00:13:42,238 --> 00:13:45,818
We broke up ages ago anyway.

231
00:13:53,330 --> 00:13:54,330
Oh, right.

232
00:13:56,230 --> 00:13:59,270
Actually, from the very beginning,

233
00:13:59,300 --> 00:14:02,040
we were never some lovey-dovey couple.

234
00:14:03,090 --> 00:14:07,940
This idiot agreed to do the documentary
without thinking about the consequences,

235
00:14:09,630 --> 00:14:13,010
so I had to play along as his boyfriend.

236
00:14:14,530 --> 00:14:17,790
But all of that ends today.

237
00:14:20,430 --> 00:14:25,460
Honestly, putting up with this
until now has been agonizing.

238
00:14:26,630 --> 00:14:29,330
I really regret agreeing to this so easily.

239
00:14:31,730 --> 00:14:33,600
Having a camera in my face all the time,

240
00:14:34,330 --> 00:14:36,030
being treated like some animal on display,

241
00:14:37,730 --> 00:14:39,440
it's just not who I am.

242
00:14:41,410 --> 00:14:44,980
Stop using other people's lives
as toys for your entertainment.

243
00:14:53,410 --> 00:14:55,090
You've read this book too, right?

244
00:14:55,930 --> 00:14:56,930
Yes...

245
00:14:57,590 --> 00:14:58,709
Us going viral on the internet,

246
00:14:58,710 --> 00:15:00,060
isn't it just like this?

247
00:15:01,530 --> 00:15:04,570
Those people who love
watching guys make out,

248
00:15:05,170 --> 00:15:08,040
they only put us on a pedestal
because we're two guys kissing.

249
00:15:08,850 --> 00:15:13,210
And they get all excited debating
who's the top and who's the bottom.

250
00:15:21,430 --> 00:15:23,590
Stop getting turned on
by other people's sex lives.

251
00:15:26,450 --> 00:15:27,890
What a joke.

252
00:15:40,830 --> 00:15:44,510
What's going to happen
to this documentary now?

253
00:15:45,470 --> 00:15:46,929
If Hasegawa-san isn't in it,

254
00:15:46,930 --> 00:15:48,350
we can't continue filming.

255
00:15:49,430 --> 00:15:50,779
But using the footage we've already shot,

256
00:15:50,780 --> 00:15:53,520
I think it might still be
possible to finish the show.

257
00:15:54,250 --> 00:15:55,250
Even so...

258
00:15:55,830 --> 00:15:58,530
we still need to get
Hasegawa-san's consent.

259
00:16:00,810 --> 00:16:01,810
True...

260
00:16:04,810 --> 00:16:05,810
No, wait.

261
00:16:06,010 --> 00:16:07,969
Don't you two think there's
something seriously wrong with you?

262
00:16:07,970 --> 00:16:08,970
What do you mean?

263
00:16:10,331 --> 00:16:14,151
If a massive earthquake hit your hometown,

264
00:16:14,630 --> 00:16:16,840
would your first worry
be about your mortgage?

265
00:16:17,370 --> 00:16:19,090
I'm sorry, what are you even talking about?

266
00:16:19,510 --> 00:16:22,270
Filming and the show should be
the last things on your mind right now.

267
00:16:23,090 --> 00:16:24,210
What on earth are you doing?

268
00:16:32,670 --> 00:16:33,670
So,

269
00:16:33,890 --> 00:16:35,250
have you gotten in touch with him?

270
00:16:35,470 --> 00:16:38,790
We've tried everything
we could this past week.

271
00:16:39,330 --> 00:16:41,000
(Day 69)
Even if we do get in touch,

272
00:16:41,030 --> 00:16:43,030
what are the chances we
can actually convince him?

273
00:16:43,990 --> 00:16:45,429
I will convince him, no matter what.

274
00:16:45,430 --> 00:16:47,940
Don't get your hopes up.

275
00:16:48,690 --> 00:16:50,010
This project...

276
00:16:50,050 --> 00:16:54,640
The producer didn't have
high expectations for it anyway.

277
00:16:55,450 --> 00:16:59,980
So I think it'll get canceled easily.

278
00:17:04,850 --> 00:17:08,620
Um... Could you let me
explain to the producer directly?

279
00:17:08,750 --> 00:17:11,690
If I can just convey the meaning of
this documentary one more time...

280
00:17:11,730 --> 00:17:16,670
In the end, they'll just tell you,
"Deadlines are more important than meaning."

281
00:17:19,310 --> 00:17:23,170
Let me handle this for now.

282
00:17:24,230 --> 00:17:27,110
Shiho, you should take a break for a while.

283
00:17:27,210 --> 00:17:28,010
Huh?

284
00:17:28,230 --> 00:17:30,650
You've been burying yourself
in this lately, haven't you?

285
00:17:30,870 --> 00:17:32,750
Go clear your head
and get some distraction.

286
00:17:33,150 --> 00:17:34,510
Like going on a date or something.

287
00:17:35,050 --> 00:17:35,830
Huh?

288
00:17:35,831 --> 00:17:37,149
Then how about we go for a drive?

289
00:17:37,150 --> 00:17:38,920
I'll drive.

290
00:17:38,990 --> 00:17:41,150
We can go to a ranch, milk
some cows, and make cheese.

291
00:17:41,220 --> 00:17:45,029
And then you two can share
some soft-serve ice cream.

292
00:17:45,030 --> 00:17:46,469
Then we go horseback riding.

293
00:17:46,470 --> 00:17:47,360
And then fall off the horse.

294
00:17:47,361 --> 00:17:48,676
And end up in the hospital, right?

295
00:17:48,700 --> 00:17:52,940
Oh, right, getting a skin
treatment would be nice too.

296
00:17:53,251 --> 00:17:55,851
I recently got some hair removal done.

297
00:17:56,040 --> 00:17:56,910
Guess where?

298
00:17:56,940 --> 00:17:57,810
Where?

299
00:17:57,811 --> 00:17:59,109
Down there.

300
00:17:59,110 --> 00:18:00,680
This is ridiculous.

301
00:18:04,310 --> 00:18:06,850
I'm trying to have a
serious conversation.

302
00:18:06,880 --> 00:18:08,550
Take this seriously.

303
00:18:08,930 --> 00:18:11,090
Stop looking down on me
just because I'm a woman.

304
00:18:15,210 --> 00:18:16,410
I'm leaving early today.

305
00:18:16,870 --> 00:18:18,070
Excuse me.

306
00:18:40,180 --> 00:18:41,200
Hello?

307
00:18:41,380 --> 00:18:42,520
Shiho?

308
00:18:44,120 --> 00:18:45,120
Naomi-san.

309
00:18:45,150 --> 00:18:46,420
I messed up.

310
00:18:47,160 --> 00:18:49,660
Just as you wanted, I failed completely.

311
00:18:50,680 --> 00:18:51,880
I'm going to resign.

312
00:18:53,559 --> 00:18:56,270
So, I won't be taking your spot anymore.

313
00:18:59,380 --> 00:19:00,380
Shiho.

314
00:19:01,220 --> 00:19:03,270
Can you come over to my place right now?

315
00:19:17,620 --> 00:19:19,660
I see.

316
00:19:20,700 --> 00:19:26,190
So, Shiho, what's on your mind right now?

317
00:19:29,740 --> 00:19:31,200
That way of asking...

318
00:19:32,570 --> 00:19:35,700
When you do interviews, Naomi-san,

319
00:19:36,440 --> 00:19:38,740
your voice is always so gentle.

320
00:19:39,780 --> 00:19:41,380
I've always loved that.

321
00:19:44,080 --> 00:19:45,080
Ah...

322
00:19:50,220 --> 00:19:51,290
Really?

323
00:19:54,720 --> 00:19:57,130
What's on your mind right now?

324
00:19:59,860 --> 00:20:01,000
Well...

325
00:20:11,170 --> 00:20:12,240
Well...

326
00:20:17,600 --> 00:20:22,320
I really hate myself.

327
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:27,020
Taking my frustration out on others,

328
00:20:28,460 --> 00:20:29,990
crying to them,

329
00:20:31,530 --> 00:20:33,030
and letting them comfort me...

330
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:37,030
Isn't that just like a typical girl?

331
00:20:38,570 --> 00:20:39,570
Hmm...

332
00:20:41,340 --> 00:20:44,270
But I think plenty of guys do that too.

333
00:20:47,700 --> 00:20:52,310
In the end, I'm the one
with the deepest prejudice.

334
00:20:54,440 --> 00:20:56,760
Obsessing over living
"unlike a typical woman,"

335
00:20:58,580 --> 00:21:00,260
assuming someone must be a certain way,

336
00:21:00,875 --> 00:21:02,555
or that someone else must "understand me."

337
00:21:03,720 --> 00:21:06,060
And then labeling them all on my own.

338
00:21:09,130 --> 00:21:10,200
Me too.

339
00:21:11,232 --> 00:21:14,442
Shutting myself at home,
overwhelmed by childcare every day,

340
00:21:15,102 --> 00:21:17,172
unable to do anything else.

341
00:21:18,480 --> 00:21:20,880
I ended up taking all that
frustration out on you, Shiho.

342
00:21:22,720 --> 00:21:25,350
Even though my husband
is the one I should be mad at.

343
00:21:33,820 --> 00:21:37,530
You weren't the one
making me miserable, Shiho.

344
00:21:42,280 --> 00:21:45,430
I think we might have had it all wrong.

345
00:21:48,660 --> 00:21:49,999
When it comes to documentaries,

346
00:21:50,306 --> 00:21:52,946
our own feelings don't matter at all.

347
00:21:53,580 --> 00:21:55,740
We are the ones who are
supposed to understand others.

348
00:21:56,740 --> 00:21:59,250
Wanting others to understand us

349
00:22:00,120 --> 00:22:02,020
is the very last thing
we should think about.

350
00:22:06,620 --> 00:22:08,620
The reason filming is stalled right now

351
00:22:09,440 --> 00:22:11,659
is simply because we've
only cared about ourselves,

352
00:22:11,660 --> 00:22:13,629
without ever trying to truly
understand what they're going through.

353
00:22:13,630 --> 00:22:15,000
This is just the karma we deserve.

354
00:22:20,901 --> 00:22:22,411
Actually, Shiho,

355
00:22:22,700 --> 00:22:26,340
you noticed that Hasegawa-san
had something on his mind too, didn't you?

356
00:22:30,840 --> 00:22:32,950
Being looked down on for being a woman,

357
00:22:35,840 --> 00:22:37,720
or things not going your way,

358
00:22:38,020 --> 00:22:39,550
that happens all the time.

359
00:22:41,740 --> 00:22:43,690
But this time, it wasn't about that.

360
00:22:55,600 --> 00:22:56,580
Hello?

361
00:22:56,581 --> 00:22:57,670
Is this Shiho-san?

362
00:22:58,170 --> 00:23:00,510
Um, I'm the middle child of three brothers,

363
00:23:00,540 --> 00:23:03,080
so I grew up in an environment
with absolutely no girls around.

364
00:23:03,260 --> 00:23:05,326
So when the president kept
prying into your private life,

365
00:23:05,350 --> 00:23:08,096
I didn't realize at all that it was
making you uncomfortable, Shiho-san.

366
00:23:08,120 --> 00:23:10,560
Ah, wait, that has nothing to
do with being the middle child.

367
00:23:11,820 --> 00:23:13,520
Uh, anyway...

368
00:23:14,720 --> 00:23:15,990
Yamada,

369
00:23:17,260 --> 00:23:19,199
didn't you say you'd take me for a drive?

370
00:23:19,200 --> 00:23:20,230
Yeah.

371
00:23:21,530 --> 00:23:22,630
Get the car.

372
00:23:45,420 --> 00:23:48,060
(Next Episode)
I want to face Hasegawa Itsuki as a person.

373
00:23:48,460 --> 00:23:49,659
Can I come along too?

374
00:23:49,660 --> 00:23:51,256
(Searching for the real you—)
That was about half a year ago, right?

375
00:23:51,280 --> 00:23:52,929
Oh, you mean Itsuki.

376
00:23:52,930 --> 00:23:55,730
What I heard sounded like a story
about a completely different person.

377
00:23:55,820 --> 00:23:58,342
If we were compatible, could
we have been the perfect couple?

378
00:23:58,380 --> 00:23:59,900
In the end, we just aren't compatible.
